38namespace webrtc {

40namespace {
41
42class ObjCVideoEncoder : public VideoEncoder {
43 public:
44 ObjCVideoEncoder(id<RTCVideoEncoder> encoder)
45 : encoder_(encoder), implementation_name_([encoder implementationName].stdString) {}
46
47 int32_t InitEncode(const VideoCodec *codec_settings, const Settings &encoder_settings) override {
48#if defined(WEBRTC_WEBKIT_BUILD)
49 int number_of_streams = SimulcastUtility::NumberOfSimulcastStreams(*codec_settings);
50 if (number_of_streams > 1) {
51 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_ERR_SIMULCAST_PARAMETERS_NOT_SUPPORTED;
52 }
53#endif
54 RTCVideoEncoderSettings *settings =
55 [[RTCVideoEncoderSettings alloc] initWithNativeVideoCodec:codec_settings];
56 return [encoder_ startEncodeWithSettings:settings
57 numberOfCores:encoder_settings.number_of_cores];
58 }
59
60 int32_t RegisterEncodeCompleteCallback(EncodedImageCallback *callback) override {
61 [encoder_ setCallback:^BOOL(RTCEncodedImage *_Nonnull frame,
62 id<RTCCodecSpecificInfo> _Nonnull info,
63 RTCRtpFragmentationHeader *_Nonnull header) {
64 if (!callback)
65 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
66 EncodedImage encodedImage = [frame nativeEncodedImage];
67
68 // Handle types that can be converted into one of CodecSpecificInfo's hard coded cases.
69 CodecSpecificInfo codecSpecificInfo;
70 // Because of symbol conflict, isKindOfClass doesn't work as expected.
71 // See https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=198782.
72 if ([NSStringFromClass([info class]) isEqual:@"WK_RTCCodecSpecificInfoH264"]) {
73 // if ([info isKindOfClass:[RTCCodecSpecificInfoH264 class]]) {
74 codecSpecificInfo = [(RTCCodecSpecificInfoH264 *)info nativeCodecSpecificInfo];
75#ifndef DISABLE_H265
76 } else if ([NSStringFromClass([info class]) isEqual:@"WK_RTCCodecSpecificInfoH265"]) {
77 // if ([info isKindOfClass:[RTCCodecSpecificInfoH265 class]]) {
78 codecSpecificInfo = [(RTCCodecSpecificInfoH265 *)info nativeCodecSpecificInfo];
79#endif
80 }
81
82 EncodedImageCallback::Result res =
83 callback->OnEncodedImage(encodedImage, &codecSpecificInfo);
84 return res.error == EncodedImageCallback::Result::OK;
85 }];
86
87 return WEBRTC_VIDEO_CODEC_OK;
88 }
89
90 int32_t Release() override { return [encoder_ releaseEncoder]; }
91
92 int32_t Encode(const VideoFrame &frame,
93 const std::vector<VideoFrameType> *frame_types) override {
94 NSMutableArray<NSNumber *> *rtcFrameTypes = [NSMutableArray array];
95 for (size_t i = 0; i < frame_types->size(); ++i) {
96 [rtcFrameTypes addObject:@(RTCFrameType(frame_types->at(i)))];
97 }
98
99 return [encoder_ encode:ToObjCVideoFrame(frame)
100 codecSpecificInfo:nil
101 frameTypes:rtcFrameTypes];
102 }
103
104 void SetRates(const RateControlParameters &parameters) override {
105 const uint32_t bitrate = parameters.bitrate.get_sum_kbps();
106 const uint32_t framerate = static_cast<uint32_t>(parameters.framerate_fps + 0.5);
107 [encoder_ setBitrate:bitrate framerate:framerate];
108 }
109
110 VideoEncoder::EncoderInfo GetEncoderInfo() const override {
111 EncoderInfo info;
112 info.supports_native_handle = true;
113 info.implementation_name = implementation_name_;
114
115 RTCVideoEncoderQpThresholds *qp_thresholds = [encoder_ scalingSettings];
116 info.scaling_settings = qp_thresholds ? ScalingSettings(qp_thresholds.low, qp_thresholds.high) :
117 ScalingSettings::kOff;
118
119 info.is_hardware_accelerated = true;
120 info.has_internal_source = false;
121 return info;
122 }
123
124 private:
125 id<RTCVideoEncoder> encoder_;
126 const std::string implementation_name_;
127};
128} // namespace
129
130ObjCVideoEncoderFactory::ObjCVideoEncoderFactory(id<RTCVideoEncoderFactory> encoder_factory)
131 : encoder_factory_(encoder_factory) {}
132
133ObjCVideoEncoderFactory::~ObjCVideoEncoderFactory() {}
134
135id<RTCVideoEncoderFactory> ObjCVideoEncoderFactory::wrapped_encoder_factory() const {
136 return encoder_factory_;
137}
138
139std::vector<SdpVideoFormat> ObjCVideoEncoderFactory::GetSupportedFormats() const {
140 std::vector<SdpVideoFormat> supported_formats;
141 for (RTCVideoCodecInfo *supportedCodec in [encoder_factory_ supportedCodecs]) {
142 SdpVideoFormat format = [supportedCodec nativeSdpVideoFormat];
143 supported_formats.push_back(format);
144 }
145
146 return supported_formats;
147}
148
149std::vector<SdpVideoFormat> ObjCVideoEncoderFactory::GetImplementations() const {
150 if ([encoder_factory_ respondsToSelector:SEL("implementations")]) {
151 std::vector<SdpVideoFormat> supported_formats;
152 for (RTCVideoCodecInfo *supportedCodec in [encoder_factory_ implementations]) {
153 SdpVideoFormat format = [supportedCodec nativeSdpVideoFormat];
154 supported_formats.push_back(format);
155 }
156 return supported_formats;
157 }
158 return GetSupportedFormats();
159}
160
161VideoEncoderFactory::CodecInfo ObjCVideoEncoderFactory::QueryVideoEncoder(
162 const SdpVideoFormat &format) const {
163
164 VideoEncoderFactory::CodecInfo codec_info;
165 codec_info.has_internal_source = false;
166 return codec_info;
167}
168
169std::unique_ptr<VideoEncoder> ObjCVideoEncoderFactory::CreateVideoEncoder(
170 const SdpVideoFormat &format) {
171 RTCVideoCodecInfo *info = [[RTCVideoCodecInfo alloc] initWithNativeSdpVideoFormat:format];
172 id<RTCVideoEncoder> encoder = [encoder_factory_ createEncoder:info];
173 // Because of symbol conflict, isKindOfClass doesn't work as expected.
174 // See https://bugs.webkit.org/show_bug.cgi?id=198782.
175 // if ([encoder isKindOfClass:[RTCWrappedNativeVideoEncoder class]]) {
176 if ([info.name isEqual:@"VP8"] || [info.name isEqual:@"VP9"]) {
177 return [(RTCWrappedNativeVideoEncoder *)encoder releaseWrappedEncoder];
178 } else {
179 return std::unique_ptr<ObjCVideoEncoder>(new ObjCVideoEncoder(encoder));
180 }
181}
